Put the fire in and put
the Russian retaliation in

00:39:11.100 --> 00:39:12.630
and you quickly
get over a billion.

00:39:12.630 --> 00:39:17.040
There were three billion then
at that time, two billion

00:39:17.040 --> 00:39:19.740
when I was born, by the
way, in 1931, three billion

00:39:19.740 --> 00:39:24.120
in 1961 when I was working
on the war plans, OK?

00:39:24.120 --> 00:39:26.030
One billion, one third.

00:39:26.030 --> 00:39:27.610
So Teller was wrong.

00:39:27.610 --> 00:39:30.730
Yes, you can get over a quarter
of the US population, a third.

00:39:30.730 --> 00:39:31.590
Let's say a third.

00:39:31.590 --> 00:39:35.830
You know, let's not
argue about a sixth here.

00:39:35.830 --> 00:39:37.510
But that's all.

00:39:37.510 --> 00:39:39.850
And Herman said in his book--
and he was a close friend

00:39:39.850 --> 00:39:40.900
of mine--

00:39:40.900 --> 00:39:44.050
he said no one would ever
build a doomsday machine.

00:39:44.050 --> 00:39:48.130
We don't have one now and
no one would build one

00:39:48.130 --> 00:39:49.420
for the following reasons.

00:39:49.420 --> 00:39:50.945
And he gave a number of reasons.

00:39:50.945 --> 00:39:51.820
You know, it's cheap.

00:39:51.820 --> 00:39:56.740
Yes, but, it has some defects.

00:39:56.740 --> 00:39:58.420
They were both wrong.

00:39:58.420 --> 00:39:59.830
Teller was wrong.

00:39:59.830 --> 00:40:00.710
Herman was wrong.

00:40:00.710 --> 00:40:02.750
Nobody's perfect.

00:40:02.750 --> 00:40:05.650
In fact, we had a
doomsday machine then.

00:40:05.650 --> 00:40:08.150
We'd had it for
10 years at least.

00:40:08.150 --> 00:40:10.570
And we have it today.

00:40:10.570 --> 00:40:13.350
If our current war
plan, the larger ones

00:40:13.350 --> 00:40:16.430
for war with Russia,
not with North Korea,

00:40:16.430 --> 00:40:18.160
but if plans for
Russia [INAUDIBLE]

00:40:18.160 --> 00:40:22.850
are carried out as
planned, then firestorms

00:40:22.850 --> 00:40:27.900
will be caused on hundreds
of cities, the smoke, which

00:40:27.900 --> 00:40:31.327
was not calculated until
1983, in terms of hundreds

00:40:31.327 --> 00:40:32.910
of millions of tons
of smoke-- and all

00:40:32.910 --> 00:40:36.540
the references in my book
or easy to get on Google.

00:40:36.540 --> 00:40:42.600
Alan Robock, R-O-B-O-C-K,
and Brian Toon, T-O-O-N.

00:40:42.600 --> 00:40:46.410
Look up their papers, especially
since 2007, confirming that,

00:40:46.410 --> 00:40:51.150
even a war between India
and Pakistan using A-bombs,

00:40:51.150 --> 00:40:54.420
Nagasaki-type bombs-- that's
all they have, like North Korea,

00:40:54.420 --> 00:40:57.480
not thermonuclear
bombs, not H-bombs--

00:40:57.480 --> 00:41:01.380
using a hundred, of which
they have many more than that,

00:41:01.380 --> 00:41:03.810
would cause firestorms
that would put enough smoke

00:41:03.810 --> 00:41:06.300
in the atmosphere
to blot out about 7%

00:41:06.300 --> 00:41:09.820
of the Earth's
sunlight globally,

00:41:09.820 --> 00:41:14.050
stop harvest, curtail harvest,
shorten growing seasons

00:41:14.050 --> 00:41:16.900
[INAUDIBLE] one, shortening
world food supply

00:41:16.900 --> 00:41:19.660
to kill what was first
estimated within a year

00:41:19.660 --> 00:41:23.110
to be about a billion
people by starvation

00:41:23.110 --> 00:41:25.161
of the most malnourished
people in the world.

00:41:25.161 --> 00:41:26.910
A year later, when
they put in the effects

00:41:26.910 --> 00:41:30.700
of Chinese soybeans, production
and some others, two billion,

00:41:30.700 --> 00:41:37.140
about 1.9 billion people, India
and Pakistan over Kashmir.

00:41:37.140 --> 00:41:40.260
But if US and Russia went
to war, the firestorms here,

00:41:40.260 --> 00:41:44.670
which I didn't explain, will
loft smoke and toxic soot,

00:41:44.670 --> 00:41:47.490
black soot, into
the stratosphere.

00:41:47.490 --> 00:41:50.950
It takes the updraft of
a special kind of fire

00:41:50.950 --> 00:41:55.800
called a firestorm to cause this
updraft to push the smoke up

00:41:55.800 --> 00:41:59.280
into the stratosphere
where it doesn't rain out

00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:01.650
and where it would quickly
go around the globe

00:42:01.650 --> 00:42:05.100
and reduce sunlight
by about 70%,

00:42:05.100 --> 00:42:08.880
causing winter-like conditions,
ice age conditions on the Earth

00:42:08.880 --> 00:42:14.620
below, ending all harvest
and starving nearly everyone.

00:42:14.620 --> 00:42:19.150
Almost, surely, not extinction
because we're so adaptable.

00:42:19.150 --> 00:42:22.090
We humans are so clever with
our clothing and our fire

00:42:22.090 --> 00:42:25.510
and our houses, we can
survive this stuff,

00:42:25.510 --> 00:42:28.575
some of us, maybe 1%,
maybe less than 1%.

00:42:28.575 --> 00:42:32.260
Well, 1% is 70 million
people, a lot of people.

00:42:32.260 --> 00:42:37.210
In Australia, eating fish
and mollusks and whatnot,

00:42:37.210 --> 00:42:37.840
it goes on.

00:42:37.840 --> 00:42:39.320
We do it all over again.

00:42:39.320 --> 00:42:43.030
But 99% of the people would
starve if we carried out

00:42:43.030 --> 00:42:46.184
our current war plan.

00:42:46.184 --> 00:42:47.850
And I was just asking
somebody at lunch,

00:42:47.850 --> 00:42:51.480
what is the chance that
we could use little bunker

00:42:51.480 --> 00:42:56.610
buster, the bombs, against
a nuclear state like Russia

00:42:56.610 --> 00:43:01.290
or North Korea, being
considered this week,

00:43:01.290 --> 00:43:06.210
and keep it localized
and limited to that?

00:43:06.210 --> 00:43:08.700
Well, the answer
was, not likely.

00:43:08.700 --> 00:43:12.230
I asked, if I may, how unlikely?

00:43:12.230 --> 00:43:14.300
Quite unlikely.

00:43:14.300 --> 00:43:17.150
And I'm right, about
very, very close to zero.

00:43:17.150 --> 00:43:18.740
Nothing is zero.

00:43:18.740 --> 00:43:20.600
We've seen, enough
things have happened

00:43:20.600 --> 00:43:22.460
that I thought were impossible.

00:43:22.460 --> 00:43:23.180
Nothing is zero.

00:43:23.180 --> 00:43:25.190
But that's very close to zero.

00:43:25.190 --> 00:43:29.320
Now, with North Korea, you
don't get nuclear winter.

00:43:29.320 --> 00:43:31.840
There's just not enough
cities there to burn.

00:43:31.840 --> 00:43:34.900
And they have only maybe
20 to 60 fission weapons.

00:43:34.900 --> 00:43:38.620
Fission weapons will
do the job over there,

00:43:38.620 --> 00:43:40.480
but it's not enough
for nuclear winter.

00:43:40.480 --> 00:43:44.260
It's not even enough to
starve one billion people.

00:43:44.260 --> 00:43:47.800
North Korea war is the one war
between two nuclear weapons

00:43:47.800 --> 00:43:50.230
states now that doesn't
have the capability

00:43:50.230 --> 00:43:53.770
to starve two billion
people or more, OK?

00:43:53.770 --> 00:43:55.100
But everyone else does.

00:43:55.100 --> 00:43:58.120
War over the Ukraine or
Syria, war with Russia,

00:43:58.120 --> 00:44:00.566
if it possibly
escalated to that,

00:44:00.566 --> 00:44:01.690
we have a doomsday machine.

00:44:01.690 --> 00:44:03.170
And they do, too.

00:44:03.170 --> 00:44:06.650
They are on hair
trigger alert, meaning

00:44:06.650 --> 00:44:09.950
that both sides believe that
if there is about to be a war

00:44:09.950 --> 00:44:14.090
or if our tactical warning,
which has often been wrong,

00:44:14.090 --> 00:44:16.580
tells us that an attack
is underway or tells them

00:44:16.580 --> 00:44:21.020
that an attack is underway,
we plan to preempt,

00:44:21.020 --> 00:44:23.120
to launch on warning.

00:44:23.120 --> 00:44:25.880
That's what Kim Jong
Un proposes to do

00:44:25.880 --> 00:44:27.260
if he's about to be attacked.

00:44:27.260 --> 00:44:29.540
That's been open
in his exercises.

00:44:29.540 --> 00:44:33.230
Today's news is that we are
contemplating a bloody nose

00:44:33.230 --> 00:44:36.770
for North Korea, an attack
on them which will hopefully

00:44:36.770 --> 00:44:37.340
be limited.

00:44:37.340 --> 00:44:39.410
We hit their missile
base, we hit their safes.

00:44:39.410 --> 00:44:40.960
We show them we are determined.

00:44:40.960 --> 00:44:42.470
We show them what the risks are.

00:44:42.470 --> 00:44:45.440
And they back off.

00:44:45.440 --> 00:44:47.990
That's what is being
considered by H.R. McMaster,

00:44:47.990 --> 00:44:52.370
supposedly recommended
by him now.

00:44:52.370 --> 00:44:56.330
Now, if I had access
to that document,

00:44:56.330 --> 00:45:01.104
I would put it out now
with the expectation

00:45:01.104 --> 00:45:02.520
that I would go
to prison for life

00:45:02.520 --> 00:45:05.570
or that I might be assassinated.

00:45:05.570 --> 00:45:07.910
But to avert that
war seems to be

00:45:07.910 --> 00:45:12.350
unquestionably worth my life,
even if my prospective life was

00:45:12.350 --> 00:45:14.000
a lot longer than it is now.

00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:17.200
It's the decision I made 40
years ago that I thought even

00:45:17.200 --> 00:45:20.180
to have a very small chance
of shortening that war,

00:45:20.180 --> 00:45:23.150
it was worth getting the
sentence I expected to get,

00:45:23.150 --> 00:45:27.010
which was 115 years in prison.

00:45:27.010 --> 00:45:31.480
It's always seemed to me,
obviously, that was worth it.

00:45:31.480 --> 00:45:33.832
I'm getting a signal here.

00:45:33.832 --> 00:45:36.940
I've got to end.

00:45:36.940 --> 00:45:38.480
Don't worry. l got you.

00:45:38.480 --> 00:45:39.300
I saw you.

00:45:42.670 --> 00:45:45.250
If we had a Snowden or a Chelsea
Manning now at a high level,

00:45:45.250 --> 00:45:47.458
I assume we'd get the-- we
are getting leaks, though,

00:45:47.458 --> 00:45:48.880
more than before.

00:45:48.880 --> 00:45:50.522
Why would I want that out?

00:45:50.522 --> 00:45:52.480
Because I think that a
lot of people would say,

00:45:52.480 --> 00:45:54.410
that's not a good idea.

00:45:54.410 --> 00:45:55.900
What would we do about it?

00:45:55.900 --> 00:45:57.790
I don't really know.

00:45:57.790 --> 00:46:02.645
With this Congress, if it was a
Democratic Congress confronting

00:46:02.645 --> 00:46:06.280
from, even a Congress as bad as
the Democratic Congress we've

00:46:06.280 --> 00:46:08.860
had over the last
10 years or so,

00:46:08.860 --> 00:46:10.750
we'd have a chance
of stopping this.

00:46:10.750 --> 00:46:14.060
I would want to see the public
saying, this must not happen.

00:46:14.060 --> 00:46:15.610
It will restart testing.

00:46:15.610 --> 00:46:17.530
It will mean that
India and Pakistan--

00:46:17.530 --> 00:46:19.030
even if North
Korea is wiped out,

00:46:19.030 --> 00:46:20.821
we don't have to worry
about them anymore--

00:46:20.821 --> 00:46:22.690
India and Pakistan,
maybe they start testing

00:46:22.690 --> 00:46:25.090
and have an H-bomb
within a year or two,

00:46:25.090 --> 00:46:30.430
which magnifies their explosive
yield by a factor of 1,000,

00:46:30.430 --> 00:46:33.560
and not good for the world.

00:46:33.560 --> 00:46:38.230
France and China increase
their MIRVs and so forth.

00:46:38.230 --> 00:46:41.110
The world, I think the chance of
getting back from the doomsday

00:46:41.110 --> 00:46:44.380
machines we have now,
after a war with Korea,

00:46:44.380 --> 00:46:50.370
is, I think, again, close to
zero, not going to happen.

00:46:50.370 --> 00:46:52.230
Why is there so
little opposition?

00:46:52.230 --> 00:46:55.110
Senator Lindsey Graham has
been saying repeatedly now

00:46:55.110 --> 00:46:58.780
on "Meet the Press" and others,
I've told the president,

00:46:58.780 --> 00:47:00.580
and he has said this
to me face-to-face,

00:47:00.580 --> 00:47:04.940
says Lindsey Graham, that,
remember, the casualties will

00:47:04.940 --> 00:47:10.860
all be over there, as
if Kim Jong Un did not

00:47:10.860 --> 00:47:15.780
have any boats with which to put
a nuclear warhead in and send

00:47:15.780 --> 00:47:19.950
them to Los Angeles or San
Francisco harbors as revenge.

00:47:19.950 --> 00:47:22.680
Which I'm, from my experience
on command and control,

00:47:22.680 --> 00:47:24.780
I am virtually
certain that it is not

00:47:24.780 --> 00:47:28.620
possible to paralyze North
Korean nuclear response

00:47:28.620 --> 00:47:31.270
by hitting their
command and control.

00:47:31.270 --> 00:47:33.160
And if the president
doesn't know that,

00:47:33.160 --> 00:47:36.060
I hope that my book
gets on "Fox &amp; Friends"

00:47:36.060 --> 00:47:39.950
and just conceivably get
that words through to him.

00:47:39.950 --> 00:47:44.260
So we're facing, in other
words, a terrible crisis

00:47:44.260 --> 00:47:46.420
right away with North
Korea, though it's not

00:47:46.420 --> 00:47:47.900
the end of the world.

00:47:47.900 --> 00:47:50.430
It's just the beginning
of the end of the world.

00:47:50.430 --> 00:47:52.444
Because what we have here--

00:47:52.444 --> 00:47:53.860
I'll just close
with this thought.

00:47:56.800 --> 00:47:58.600
It hasn't happened yet.

00:47:58.600 --> 00:48:00.520
So people can look
at the last 70 years

00:48:00.520 --> 00:48:02.590
and say, well, it
wasn't certain.

00:48:02.590 --> 00:48:03.550
That's for sure.

00:48:03.550 --> 00:48:05.220
It was even highly likely.

00:48:05.220 --> 00:48:06.490
That gets to be hard to say.

00:48:06.490 --> 00:48:09.460
I personally think, in fact,
that it was highly likely

00:48:09.460 --> 00:48:12.690
that this blow up and that we've
had something like a miracle.

00:48:12.690 --> 00:48:14.760
And miracles do happen.

00:48:14.760 --> 00:48:17.970
It's a miracle that I'm
not in jail right now.

00:48:17.970 --> 00:48:19.050
That's another story.

00:48:19.050 --> 00:48:20.310
But it was not likely.

00:48:20.310 --> 00:48:23.340
It was extremely unlikely
that I would not be in jail.

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:25.812
It was a miracle that
Nelson Mandela made it

00:48:25.812 --> 00:48:27.020
without a violent revolution.

00:48:27.020 --> 00:48:30.990
It was a miracle that the
Berlin Wall came down,

00:48:30.990 --> 00:48:32.700
all of this before your time.

00:48:32.700 --> 00:48:38.100
Almost even hard to imagine
how impossible that was.

00:48:38.100 --> 00:48:40.860
I don't think I've
ever met a person in,

00:48:40.860 --> 00:48:45.480
let's say, who in 1980, if
asked that the Berlin Wall would

00:48:45.480 --> 00:48:52.054
be down in 1989, that would not
have said, that's impossible.

00:48:52.054 --> 00:48:53.970
If anybody knows of any
contradiction of that,

00:48:53.970 --> 00:48:55.410
it did happen.

00:48:55.410 --> 00:48:57.270
So we can change.

00:48:57.270 --> 00:48:59.170
Change like that can happen.

00:48:59.170 --> 00:49:02.490
I think it has to be as dramatic
as happened in the Soviet

00:49:02.490 --> 00:49:03.840
Union.

00:49:03.840 --> 00:49:05.820
It has to be a
change of attitudes,

00:49:05.820 --> 00:49:11.200
as happened in terms of white
majority rule being allowable

00:49:11.200 --> 00:49:13.050
in South Africa.

00:49:13.050 --> 00:49:13.950
Is that likely?

00:49:13.950 --> 00:49:15.620
No.

00:49:15.620 --> 00:49:16.490
It's unlikely.

00:49:16.490 --> 00:49:19.210
It's very unlikely.

00:49:19.210 --> 00:49:21.734
But it's not impossible.

00:49:21.734 --> 00:49:23.400
And I think what we're
talking about now

00:49:23.400 --> 00:49:25.771
is the future of
civilization, of humanity.

00:49:25.771 --> 00:49:27.270
It's the kind of
subject that I know

00:49:27.270 --> 00:49:31.670
people here do, think big
about, rightly so, all the time.

00:49:31.670 --> 00:49:34.100
But if you haven't been thinking
about this, which is also

00:49:34.100 --> 00:49:37.280
very possible,
I'd say this, too,

00:49:37.280 --> 00:49:41.450
has to be added to the list
of existential dangers.

00:49:41.450 --> 00:49:44.960
As for climate, somebody
asked me last night

00:49:44.960 --> 00:49:49.720
about artificial intelligence,
germ warfare, whatever.

00:49:49.720 --> 00:49:53.000
Our current ready
doomsday machines,

00:49:53.000 --> 00:49:56.660
which are about
to be refurbished

00:49:56.660 --> 00:50:00.680
at the expense of
$1.5 trillion--

00:50:00.680 --> 00:50:03.770
strictly $1.2 trillion, but
they say, with inflation,

00:50:03.770 --> 00:50:07.850
really $1.6 trillion
over the next 30 years--

00:50:07.850 --> 00:50:11.000
and in Russia,
where using it would

00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:14.990
be just as insane as here--

00:50:14.990 --> 00:50:16.580
and it would have
been and almost came

00:50:16.580 --> 00:50:18.920
close to happening
several times in the past.

00:50:18.920 --> 00:50:22.030
And you would not be here
and I would not be here.

00:50:22.030 --> 00:50:25.730
I participated in the
Cuban Missile Crisis.

00:50:25.730 --> 00:50:27.890
I was wrong about nearly
everything involved,

00:50:27.890 --> 00:50:30.650
as was everybody
dealing with me.

00:50:30.650 --> 00:50:32.210
And if my own
instincts, like those

00:50:32.210 --> 00:50:35.690
of JFK's initial instincts
to attack those missiles--

00:50:35.690 --> 00:50:39.590
I wasn't precisely on that, but
I was ready to see it happen--

00:50:39.590 --> 00:50:43.900
had been followed,
we would not be here.

00:50:43.900 --> 00:50:46.370
Doomsday would have
resulted from any time

00:50:46.370 --> 00:50:50.300
since about 1950, when
Harry Truman left Eisenhower

00:50:50.300 --> 00:50:54.080
with 1,000 fission weapons.

00:50:54.080 --> 00:51:00.140
Eisenhower left office and left
Kennedy 23,000 thermonuclear

00:51:00.140 --> 00:51:05.260
weapons, which Kennedy and
Johnson raised to 37,000,

00:51:05.260 --> 00:51:08.410
at a time when Herb York, the
director of Livermore Labs,

00:51:08.410 --> 00:51:10.450
used to say, how
many weapons does it

00:51:10.450 --> 00:51:14.320
take to deter a nuclear
attack against an enemy

00:51:14.320 --> 00:51:16.760
rational enough to be deterred?

00:51:16.760 --> 00:51:18.070
One.

00:51:18.070 --> 00:51:26.166
Or if that's not enough, 10,
but closer to 10 or 1 than 100.

00:51:26.166 --> 00:51:27.770
37,000.

00:51:27.770 --> 00:51:31.340
We've cut that way down
now, to about 4,000 each.

00:51:31.340 --> 00:51:35.470
It takes several hundred
to cause nuclear winter.

00:51:35.470 --> 00:51:38.470
So we're in a galaxy
now that may not

00:51:38.470 --> 00:51:42.280
have a very long history
as far as human habitation

00:51:42.280 --> 00:51:45.700
is concerned, except for
a very small remnant.

00:51:45.700 --> 00:51:49.810
And that's the
challenge here that I

00:51:49.810 --> 00:51:55.630
add to your global ambitions,
to try to dismantle the doomsday

00:51:55.630 --> 00:52:00.220
machines on earth and to
move toward what Trump calls

00:52:00.220 --> 00:52:02.460
the world coming to its senses.

00:52:02.460 --> 00:52:03.814
Thank you.

00:52:03.814 --> 00:52:06.299
[APPLAUSE]

00:52:12.760 --> 00:52:14.251
I've used up the time here.

00:52:14.251 --> 00:52:16.260
I know a lot of you
have to go to work.

00:52:16.260 --> 00:52:19.710
I can stay longer,
until even 2:20 or so.

00:52:19.710 --> 00:52:23.575
And there's a few more
minutes, even formally--

00:52:23.575 --> 00:52:24.141
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:52:24.141 --> 00:52:25.140
Thank you for your talk.

00:52:25.140 --> 00:52:28.260
It was extremely cheery.

00:52:28.260 --> 00:52:31.200
Do you see anything
actionable that people

00:52:31.200 --> 00:52:34.440
who already have careers and
can't exactly immediately jump

00:52:34.440 --> 00:52:39.210
into civil service can
do to impact any of this?

00:52:39.210 --> 00:52:41.070
DANIEL ELLSBERG: Yeah,
could you hear that?

00:52:41.070 --> 00:52:43.830
I have to go up to hear it.

00:52:43.830 --> 00:52:46.070
You know, I have to say
that the first thing, you're

00:52:46.070 --> 00:52:47.861
talking to people who
already have careers,

00:52:47.861 --> 00:52:50.060
have civil service and so forth.

00:52:50.060 --> 00:52:52.930
I was asked this question
just the other day

00:52:52.930 --> 00:52:54.980
by an Italian journalist,
it so happens.

00:52:54.980 --> 00:52:59.740
And my real answer is leak.

00:52:59.740 --> 00:53:02.440
It's actually, don't
just tell your bosses

00:53:02.440 --> 00:53:05.860
what you know that you think
the public ought to know.

00:53:05.860 --> 00:53:07.870
Don't leave it to
your bosses to decide

00:53:07.870 --> 00:53:10.120
what the public should know.

00:53:10.120 --> 00:53:12.490
Be prepared to
reveal that yourself.

00:53:12.490 --> 00:53:13.870
Do it anonymously.

00:53:13.870 --> 00:53:16.810
Cover your tracks, if you
can put out enough that way

00:53:16.810 --> 00:53:18.460
to make the point.

00:53:18.460 --> 00:53:20.320
Chelsea Manning
and Ed Snowden knew

00:53:20.320 --> 00:53:23.080
they couldn't put out enough
to make their point without,

00:53:23.080 --> 00:53:27.550
in effect, either revealing
themselves or pointing

00:53:27.550 --> 00:53:29.400
the finger of
suspicion at others.

00:53:29.400 --> 00:53:33.220
So like myself, they determined
they would say who had done it.

00:53:33.220 --> 00:53:33.970
That's what I did.

00:53:33.970 --> 00:53:36.050
I didn't want others
to be blamed for it.

00:53:36.050 --> 00:53:40.660
But I would say that should
not be kept within channels.

00:53:40.660 --> 00:53:43.720
We're in a situation
now where sharing

00:53:43.720 --> 00:53:47.810
that wrongly-held information
is of the highest importance.

00:53:47.810 --> 00:53:50.830
And so I'm talking to an
audience now here, unusually,

00:53:50.830 --> 00:53:54.580
which will be or is in a
chance to actually make

00:53:54.580 --> 00:53:56.920
that kind of difference,
generally not.

00:53:56.920 --> 00:53:58.900
But for many years,
I didn't talk

00:53:58.900 --> 00:54:01.570
about whistleblowing at all
when I talked about activism.

00:54:01.570 --> 00:54:05.200
For 40 years, I spent my
time not writing this book

00:54:05.200 --> 00:54:07.180
but trying to build
an anti-war movement,

00:54:07.180 --> 00:54:08.740
an anti-nuclear
movement, that would

00:54:08.740 --> 00:54:11.290
be like the anti-war movement
that had helped end the Vietnam

00:54:11.290 --> 00:54:15.190
War, with some success during
the Freeze Movement, though it,

00:54:15.190 --> 00:54:19.259
in the end, didn't change
this arms race significantly.

00:54:19.259 --> 00:54:20.800
It only lowered the
number of weapons

00:54:20.800 --> 00:54:26.522
by 80%, which made no difference
at all, no difference.

00:54:26.522 --> 00:54:27.730
There would be no difference.

00:54:27.730 --> 00:54:29.104
If the war occurred,
you wouldn't

00:54:29.104 --> 00:54:32.080
tell whether it had been done
with 8,000 weapons or 40,000

00:54:32.080 --> 00:54:33.220
weapons.

00:54:33.220 --> 00:54:35.590
If there was somebody alive
to decide and try to tell,

00:54:35.590 --> 00:54:37.610
they wouldn't be able
to tell the difference.

00:54:37.610 --> 00:54:39.200
So that didn't work.

00:54:39.200 --> 00:54:41.150
But I didn't talk about
whistleblowing much,

00:54:41.150 --> 00:54:42.910
mainly because people
I was talking to

00:54:42.910 --> 00:54:44.890
would not have a
chance to put that out,

00:54:44.890 --> 00:54:47.057
but also because it
seemed self-serving.

00:54:47.057 --> 00:54:48.640
And then I thought
of a way to say it,

00:54:48.640 --> 00:54:52.050
which I have been saying
and I'll say for 10 years.

00:54:52.050 --> 00:54:54.760
Don't do what I did.

00:54:54.760 --> 00:54:59.260
Don't wait till the bombs are
falling or thousands of people

00:54:59.260 --> 00:55:03.280
more have died if you
have information that

00:55:03.280 --> 00:55:07.970
could avert these catastrophes.

00:55:07.970 --> 00:55:12.110
No matter the cost
to yourself, consider

00:55:12.110 --> 00:55:13.730
paying that cost to put it out.

00:55:13.730 --> 00:55:18.950
Because a war's worth
of lives is at stake.

00:55:18.950 --> 00:55:20.290
AUDIENCE: In 1983--

00:55:20.290 --> 00:55:22.989
I think it was 1983-- there was
a movie called "The Day After"

00:55:22.989 --> 00:55:24.280
starring John Lithgow, set in--

00:55:24.280 --> 00:55:25.196
DANIEL ELLSBERG: Yeah.

00:55:25.196 --> 00:55:27.772
AUDIENCE: --Manhattan, Kansas
after nuclear war with Russia.

00:55:27.772 --> 00:55:30.230
It is said that this movie was
screened by the Joint Chiefs

00:55:30.230 --> 00:55:32.605
a day or two before it was
actually shown on broadcast TV

00:55:32.605 --> 00:55:34.880
and that, prior to this, the
Joint Chiefs had operated

00:55:34.880 --> 00:55:37.820
under the idea that nuclear
war was quote, winnable,

00:55:37.820 --> 00:55:40.390
that there is this concept
of minimal acceptable losses

00:55:40.390 --> 00:55:42.320
and that this movie
changed their mind.

00:55:42.320 --> 00:55:44.690
Do you agree with
this, disagree?

00:55:44.690 --> 00:55:48.300
Has the war planning at the
top about acceptable losses

00:55:48.300 --> 00:55:49.164
evolved over time?

00:55:49.164 --> 00:55:49.830
Or is it still--

00:55:49.830 --> 00:55:50.375
DANIEL ELLSBERG: OK.

00:55:50.375 --> 00:55:50.810
AUDIENCE: --screwed
up like it was--

00:55:50.810 --> 00:55:52.268
DANIEL ELLSBERG:
You can hear that?

00:55:52.268 --> 00:55:54.090
I hear it with difficulty.

00:55:54.090 --> 00:55:57.360
I've never heard before that
the Joint Chiefs saw it before,

00:55:57.360 --> 00:55:58.100
during, or after.

00:55:58.100 --> 00:56:00.590
I've never heard the Joint
Chiefs connected with it.

00:56:00.590 --> 00:56:02.870
Did the Joint Chiefs
believe it was winnable?

00:56:02.870 --> 00:56:05.990
Yes, the way they thought
Vietnam was winnable.

00:56:05.990 --> 00:56:09.050
In other words, in a virtually,
literally meaningless way.

00:56:09.050 --> 00:56:11.990
They always talked about
prevailing, about winning.

00:56:11.990 --> 00:56:14.330
There were years when they
didn't so much and then

00:56:14.330 --> 00:56:16.120
other years they did prevail.

00:56:16.120 --> 00:56:17.930
What does prevail mean?

00:56:17.930 --> 00:56:20.720
I think it was Weinberger
who said at one point,

00:56:20.720 --> 00:56:23.800
it's a word that sounds
better than the opposite,

00:56:23.800 --> 00:56:25.190
than not doing, not prevailing.

00:56:25.190 --> 00:56:27.260
But what does it mean?

00:56:27.260 --> 00:56:30.500
If it meant anything, it
meant reducing the damage

00:56:30.500 --> 00:56:34.160
that the other side is
capable of doing to you, OK?

00:56:34.160 --> 00:56:37.610
So if you get rid of
their land-based missiles,

00:56:37.610 --> 00:56:40.730
they still will have enough
submarine-based missiles

00:56:40.730 --> 00:56:44.180
to destroy our society, but
they won't have the land base.

00:56:44.180 --> 00:56:46.900
So that's worth doing, isn't it?

00:56:46.900 --> 00:56:50.740
Well, no, you know, it isn't.

00:56:50.740 --> 00:56:52.050
So why are you doing this?

00:56:52.050 --> 00:56:54.850
Why are you talking about
renewing our land-based ICBMs,

00:56:54.850 --> 00:56:56.710
which are totally
vulnerable to attack,

00:56:56.710 --> 00:56:59.440
in order to get their land-based
ICBMs, which are totally

00:56:59.440 --> 00:57:01.750
vulnerable to attack?

00:57:01.750 --> 00:57:04.150
Because Lockheed
Martin makes them.

00:57:04.150 --> 00:57:08.950
There's jobs, profits,
local real estate.

00:57:08.950 --> 00:57:11.710
The weapons have to be on
hot alert, not soft alert,

00:57:11.710 --> 00:57:14.680
around the clock,
so that we can sell

00:57:14.680 --> 00:57:18.910
more restaurant food or
whatever the hell else in North

00:57:18.910 --> 00:57:21.280
Dakota and Wyoming and Montana.

00:57:21.280 --> 00:57:24.190
There is no strategic
rationale for them, whatever.

00:57:24.190 --> 00:57:26.500
But that's enough.

00:57:26.500 --> 00:57:29.650
So the Joint Chiefs were not,
I think, as far as I know,

00:57:29.650 --> 00:57:31.460
not affected by that at all.

00:57:31.460 --> 00:57:33.100
And if you pressed
them as whether they

00:57:33.100 --> 00:57:35.320
could win more than what
I've just described,

00:57:35.320 --> 00:57:36.370
they would say, no.

00:57:36.370 --> 00:57:37.420
But that's something.

00:57:37.420 --> 00:57:39.710
We've got to do something,
not just nothing.

00:57:39.710 --> 00:57:44.140
And that was, in
effect, silliness.

00:57:44.140 --> 00:57:45.820
Of course, it's the
kind of silliness

00:57:45.820 --> 00:57:47.980
that may doom our species.

00:57:47.980 --> 00:57:50.330
And it's not only
in this country.

00:57:50.330 --> 00:57:53.260
However, the movie
"The Day After"

00:57:53.260 --> 00:57:56.180
was shown to Ronald Reagan.

00:57:56.180 --> 00:57:57.580
And it did have a big effect.

00:57:57.580 --> 00:58:00.280
He couldn't go into the
office at all the next day.

00:58:00.280 --> 00:58:03.100
He said he stayed in
bed and he felt sick.

00:58:03.100 --> 00:58:05.890
And that it very much
affected his mind when he went

00:58:05.890 --> 00:58:09.950
into discussions with Gorbachev
of ending all nuclear weapons,

00:58:09.950 --> 00:58:14.170
ballistic missiles of all kinds,
which didn't happen because he

00:58:14.170 --> 00:58:18.580
had the crazy belief of an
umbrella-like Strategic Defense

00:58:18.580 --> 00:58:19.540
Initiative, SDI--

00:58:19.540 --> 00:58:22.810
Star Wars-- that would
protect us entirely

00:58:22.810 --> 00:58:25.490
and he wasn't
willing to give up.

00:58:25.490 --> 00:58:27.437
He wasn't willing
to give that up

00:58:27.437 --> 00:58:28.770
and couldn't get that agreement.

00:58:28.770 --> 00:58:29.561
That's another one.

00:58:29.561 --> 00:58:31.330
So it had an effect on Reagan.

00:58:31.330 --> 00:58:32.770
Gorbachev, meanwhile,
had already

00:58:32.770 --> 00:58:34.480
been influenced by
nuclear weapons.

00:58:34.480 --> 00:58:39.460
And, by the way, "The Day After"
is just a tiny, little sliver

00:58:39.460 --> 00:58:42.190
of what the actual
consequences of a nuclear war

00:58:42.190 --> 00:58:44.080
would look like.

00:58:44.080 --> 00:58:47.350
Movies that have come
closer to that, there's one

00:58:47.350 --> 00:58:49.780
called "Threads" in England
that they've never allowed

00:58:49.780 --> 00:58:52.550
to be on BBC, to be shown.

00:58:52.550 --> 00:58:54.490
And again, it
really just focuses

00:58:54.490 --> 00:58:57.680
on the long-term degradation
and disintegration

00:58:57.680 --> 00:59:01.450
of everything, like Cormac
McCarthy's "The Road,"

00:59:01.450 --> 00:59:02.170
pretty much.

00:59:02.170 --> 00:59:06.010
So no nuclear
state has ever been

00:59:06.010 --> 00:59:08.890
willing to tell its
own people or to hold

00:59:08.890 --> 00:59:14.010
others accountable to the risks
we are posing over their head.

00:59:14.010 --> 00:59:18.910
And a movie like that today
would be very worthwhile.

00:59:18.910 --> 00:59:21.825
But I don't know what
prospect there is of it.

00:59:21.825 --> 00:59:23.200
AUDIENCE: And,
once again, please

00:59:23.200 --> 00:59:25.450
say thank you to
Mr. Daniel Ellsberg.

00:59:25.450 --> 00:59:26.950
[APPLAUSE]

00:59:26.950 --> 00:59:28.450
DANIEL ELLSBERG: That's OK.

00:59:28.450 --> 00:59:30.300
Thank you.

